******
[5]
Date: 23 Jul 2015
Source: Focus Information Agency [edited]
http://www.focus-fen.net/news/2015/07/23/378632/strengthened-measures-required-over-anthrax-positive-tested-surfaces-of-the-appliances-in-a-slaughterhouse-minster.html


"Strengthened measures have been imposed over anthrax positive tested surfaces of the appliances in a slaughterhouse in Varna." That is what Minister of Agriculture and Food, Desislava Taneva, told journalists, a reporter of FOCUS News Agency announced. "Precautionary measures have been taken against possible risk in the retail stores, which hadn't been in touch with the infected meat," the Minister said.

Desislava Taneva specified that the anthrax-diseased animal was slaughtered on 7 Jul 2015. "The disease was confirmed after the death of the farmer who [had] slaughtered the animal. The farmer slaughtered a sick animal. A private practitioner veterinarian [had] not been informed that there was a sick animal. The animal was slaughtered at night and then was given to other persons absolutely illegally," she said.

According to her, the response was delayed because neither the farmer nor the veterinary doctor met their obligation to inform the respective authorities on the case. "Absolutely all measures were taken immediately after the news about the disease emerged."

Now all retail stores, restaurants and meat shops in the district [are being inconvenienced], as they haven't sold or were supplied meat from diseased animals. However, they all have been closed for disinfection," she said. "The reason for these more stringent measures and closing off the sites were positive samples from the surface of the equipment in the cutting plant," the Minister specified.

--
