[Before someone corrects me, "anthrax" is the disease, _Bacillus anthracis_ is the aetiologic pathogen causing the disease. Folks get careless using the former to cover both subjects.

But having said that, I for one am very impressed by 2 things to do with this incident. The thoroughness and speed of the government response and the quick reporting by the Bulgarian news agencies. Unfortunately not too common on either score these days for many of us. Once I saw that sausages and meatballs were involved, it was clear that there would be contamination spread through mincing and mixing the meat and viscera. If you go to either of the first 2 articles above, there are pictures of the different sausages. Minister Taneva and her people are to be commended. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3531777,81.]
